        <content>
          <p>SECTION 6.  INTERRUPTION AND SUSPENSION OF
LIBERATIVE PRESCRIPTION
Art. 3503.  Solidary obligors
When prescription is interrupted against a solidary obligor, the interruption is effective against all solidary obligors and their successors.
When prescription is interrupted against a successor of a solidary obligor, the interruption is effective against other successors if the obligation is indivisible.  If the obligation is divisible, the interruption is effective against other successors only for the portions for which they are bound.</p>
        </content>
